{"title":"DT Swiss’ New Gravel Dynamo Hub and Front Wheels","link":"https://theradavist.com/dt-swiss-dynamo-hub-and-front-wheels/","date":1732115300000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Keyvisual_241022_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Keyvisual_241022_1920px.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Keyvisual_241022_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Keyvisual_241022_1920px.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/dt-swiss/\" target=\"_blank\">DT Swiss</a> enters the world of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/dynamo/\" target=\"_blank\">dynamo</a> lighting with its new 350 SP PL-7 hub ($236.90) and two front wheel options, G 1600 Spline Dyn ($442.90) and G 1800 Spline Dyn ($342.90). Let’s check them out…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8833_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8833_1920px.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8833_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8833_1920px.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>DT Swiss Dynamo Technology</h3>\n<p>Dynamo hubs are ideally efficient, durable, and compatible, nesting in with available bikes in any given market with plug-and-play ease. DT Swiss embraced gravel bikes for its new 350 SP PL-7 hub design, allowing users to ride at night with infinite power.</p>\n<p><img width=\"2306\" height=\"1118\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?fit=1200,1118&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?w=2306&amp;quality=75 2306w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?resize=1200,582&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?resize=2000,970&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?resize=768,372&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?resize=1536,745&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_01.jpg?resize=2048,993&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><br />\n<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2306\" height=\"1118\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?fit=1200,1118&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?w=2306&amp;quality=75 2306w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?resize=1200,582&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?resize=2000,970&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?resize=768,372&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?resize=1536,745&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Effeciency_DT_Dynamo_02.jpg?resize=2048,993&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<h3>Efficiency</h3>\n<p>DT’s dynamo hub offers incredibly efficient power generation with minimum drag. With the SP PL-7 generator, riders can achieve an efficiency of 72% at 15 km/h, while delivering a 6V3W standard output.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8332_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8332_1920px.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8332_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Action_8332_1920px.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Durability</h3>\n<p>With a tailor-made hub shell, you can rely on the build quality you have come to expect from DT Swiss hubs, while benefiting from our global network of service centers for a seamless customer journey.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_004_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_004_1920px.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_004_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_004_1920px.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Compatibility</h3>\n<p>This new Dynamo Hub is StVZO compliant and has a 6V3W rating, ensuring compatibility with standard hub dynamo products, including dynamo lamps and converters for USB-powered devices. It uses a thru-axle mount for modern gravel bikes and is non-boost-spaced.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_G_1800_GR_1600_002_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_G_1800_GR_1600_002_1920px.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_G_1800_GR_1600_002_1920px.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/DTSwiss_Dynamo_Hub_Detail_SP_PL_7_Hub_G_1800_GR_1600_002_1920px.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Products</h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/350SP_Hub.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/350SP_Hub.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/350SP_Hub.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/350SP_Hub.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1600.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1600.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1600.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1600.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1800.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1800.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1800.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/GR1800.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.dtswiss.com/en/innovations/bring-new-adventures-to-light\" target=\"_blank\">DT Swiss</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/dt-swiss-dynamo-hub-and-front-wheels/\">DT Swiss’ New Gravel Dynamo Hub and Front Wheels</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"246cf351e71dfeefb6f08a0b0a675a177ba704ce5b3d4466ada1659eb9f78d54","category":"Cycling"}